jobs.title: Electrical Apprentice
jobs.description:
Work will be performed as it applies to installation, alterations, additions and/or repairs of electrical systems, conductors and associated materials and equipment customarily installed within the commercial and industrial electrical construction industries. All work must be completed in compliance with the requirements of the National Electrical Code and other state and local building codes, as applicable. Tasks will vary depending on the apprenticeship level.

There are four (4) levels of Apprentices. At each level the Apprentice must complete 2,000 hours of electrically related work as identified in the Specific Job Responsibilities section and participate in on-the-job training. Additionally, at each level the Apprentice must attend 150 hours of formal classroom instruction each school year and achieve a minimum passing grade of 70.

jobs.description: We are looking for an Office manager to organize and coordinate administration duties and office procedures. Ultimately, the Office manager should be able to ensure the smooth running of the office and help to improve company procedures and day-to-day operation.
